|-------|----------|----------|---------|
| 1. Credential Decryption | CRITICAL | CrawlSourceService.java | Credentials encrypted but never decrypted on retrieval |
| 2. API Contract Mismatch | HIGH | test_submission_ownership.sh line 148 | Test calls `/api/grading/submissions/{id}` expecting Submission ID but endpoint expects GradingState ID |
| 3. Authorization Logic Flaw | MEDIUM | SubmissionService.java line 121-143 | getSubmission() has redundant condition; logic structure is confusing and error-prone |
| 4. Weak Key Padding | MEDIUM | AesEncryptionUtil.java line 56-63 | Null-byte padding reduces entropy if key is shorter than 32 bytes |
| 5. CORS Hardcoded | LOW | CorsConfig.java | CORS origins hardcoded; no production override mechanism |
| 6. Restrictive Security Filter | LOW | SecurityConfig.java line 43 | denyAll() blocks necessary non-API endpoints |
| 7. Undersized Thread Pools | LOW | AsyncConfig.java | Core pool size of 2 for crawls; no explicit rejection policy |

